      "content": "I see what you mean about the stability, but it's just so unpredictable here. It literally feels like the whole system is being undermined by some kind of unseen force or just complete disorder. Honestly, it feels like there's something actively working against the logic of the schedule. Is there a way to protect my itinerary from that kind of randomness?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When the system feels actively against you, you need to build a personal shield against the randomness. The best way to protect your itinerary from unseen disorder is to secure the most flexible booking you can find. Look for tickets that offer the most generous change or cancellation policies, even if they cost a bit more upfront. This gives you the power to pivot when the next wave of chaos hits.\n\nAlso, try to get concrete confirmation from a human agent—a ticket desk representative, not just a chatbot. Explain your situation and ask them to *manually* book you onto the next viable option, rather than letting the automated system assign you to the next available slot. A human agent can sometimes see the \"back-end\" logic that the public-facing screens hide.\n\nThis is a battle against entropy, and in travel, the best defense is often a well-placed, slightly more expensive, but robust plan. You need to be the master of your own small patch of stability amidst the airport's general mayhem.",
